commit.message: bump version to 0.8.1

more specific error codes (#40)

instead of returning `OMEMO_ERR_MALFORMED_BUNDLE` or `OMEMO_ERR_MALFORMED_XML` for all kinds of errors, each type of error that can occur now has its own error code.
for errors that really are the same and therefore still return the same error code, some additional output can be turned on via an env var.

this should help debugging some issues and closes #35.

commit.message: CHANGELOG.md: Document this pull request
README.md: CMake-ify
README.md: Improve section on dependencies
Makefile: Drop
Actions: Build for Windows using msys2
Actions: Migrate from Makefile to CMake and Ninja
Add CMake build system (including a fixed pkg-config template)
tests: Make tests use . rather than test/ for SQLite files
bump version 0.8.0

fix flaky test test_aes_gcm_encrypt_decrypt

this resolves #39
the static value `0x00` was used to try and change the variable ciphertext and provoke an authentication failure.
since encryption depends on random data, the modified byte presumably
sometimes ended up being `0x00` even before the change, resulting in
authentication success and test failure.

use namespace from XEP and remove ability to set it at build time

since the XEP was officially accepted, the "untraditional" namespace
became the official one.

mention the exact version implemented in the README

it's 0.3.0
this closes #26.

Makefile: Fix crosscompilation installing to wrong directory

By using $(CC) instead of hardcoding gcc we make sure to get the
correct triplet that is being used for the installation directory.

Credits go to Helmut Grohne for providing a fix, see
https://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=1003476
Make GitHub Dependabot keep our GitHub Actions up to date
Add GitHub Action for Linux build
add function to check a key's prekey attribute
update changelog

implement function to add recipient with prekey attribute

this fixes #28.
Add missing symlinks libomemo.so.$(VER_MAJ) and libomemo.so
bump version to 0.7.1
